The paper discusses a new approximation method for Gaussian process regression, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper specifically addresses the limitations of the method in high dimensional data sets and input-dependent noise, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely sub-category as it is the most general and covers a wide range of topics related to supervised learning.
